    "faq_r34eXF": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question_qUVctq": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What precious metals do you use?",
            "answer": "<p>Promise stones come in sterling silver with rhodium plating OR 2.5 microns of 18ct gold-plating, known as Gold Vermeil</p><p>All pieces are engraved with 925 for metal authenticity and our \"The Promise Co\" engraving for quality assurance</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_Xc3Djz": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What stones do you use?",
            "answer": "<p>Our pieces feature conflict-free simulated diamonds, hand-set stones for a flawless finish</p><p>Our Promise stones boast a 2.18 refractive index, MOHS rating of 8.5, perfect for everyday wear with care</p><p>To compare: Diamonds have a 2.41 refractive index and MOHS rating of 10, Swarovski Crystals sit at around 1.6 refractive index, MOHS 6-7</p><p>We aim to provide diamond-like sparkle at a fraction of the cost, using our exclusive clear or emerald cut patterns for enhanced clarity</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_mCRrcW": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is Gold Vermeil?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>(Pronounced Ver-may!)</strong></p><p>Gold Vermeil is not to be mixed up with normal gold plating… it is a thick layer of solid 18ct Gold on top of Sterling Silver base, meaning you get the look and feel of solid gold at a fraction of the price!</p><p>We use 18ct gold that is a minimum of 2.5 microns thick, as required by the Federal Trade Commission to classify vermeil, layered over sterling silver. </p><p><strong>Did you know?</strong> Plating as thin as 0.1 microns can still be classed as Gold Plated!? Our plating is 25 times thicker than this (crazy right)</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_Yyy8rx": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I care for Gold Vermeil?",
            "answer": "<p>Gold Vermeil is resilient, but for lasting shine:</p><ul><li>Minimise exposure to sweat and water</li><li>Remove before exercising or washing hands</li><li>Avoid perfumes and lotions</li><li>Be gentle when using hand sanitiser</li><li>Clean with a dry cloth</li><li>Store in a dry place when not worn for daily protection</li><li>Do not wear your ring in the pool, harsh chemicals and Chlorine can cause corrosion</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "question_G6whAK": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is Sterling Silver?",
            "answer": "<p>925 Sterling Silver is an alloy made of 92.5% pure silver and 7.5% copper. To make sure your Sterling Silver </p><p>On top of a sterling silver base we plate jewellery in rhodium, which makes your ring extra durable and shiny. Rhodium is one of the costliest precious metals due to its rarity</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_76YTdb": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I care for Sterling Silver?",
            "answer": "<p>Sterling Silver is perfect for everyday wear, but to ensure your ring lasts as long as possible:</p><ul><li>Remove before exercising, washing hands, or showering</li><li>Polish gently with a silver cloth for tarnished jewellery</li><li>Skip perfumes and lotions while wearing</li><li>Be cautious with hand sanitiser</li><li>Store in a dry place when not worn</li><li>Do not wear your ring in the pool, harsh chemicals and Chlorine can cause corrosion</li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
